extends layout

block content
	article.jqm-content(data-role='content')
		h1 Buttons
		a.jqm-api-link(href='http://api.jquerymobile.com/button/', data-ajax='false', data-role='button', data-inline='true', data-mini='true', data-icon='arrow-r', data-iconpos='right') API
		p.jqm-intro
			| Buttons are core widgets in jQuery Mobile and are used within a wide range of other
			| plugins. The button markup is flexible and can be created from links or form buttons.
		h2#button-markup Basic markup
		p
			| Use anchor links (
			code a
			| elements) to mark up navigation buttons, and
			code input
			| or
			code button
			| elements for form submission. By default, all buttons in the body content are styled as block-level elements
			| so they fill the width of the screen:
		div(data-demo-html='true')
			a(href='#', data-role='button') Anchor
			form
				button Button
				input(type='button', value='Input')
				input(type='submit', value='Submit')
				input(type='reset', value='Reset')
		h2#button-inline Inline
		p
			| If you have multiple buttons that should sit side-by-side on the same line, add the
			code data-inline="true"
			| attribute to each button. This will style the buttons to be the width of
			| their content so the buttons sit on the same line.
		div(data-demo-html='true')
			p
				a(href='#', data-role='button', data-inline='true') True
				a(href='#', data-role='button', data-inline='true') False
		h2#button-theme Theme
		p
			| Buttons can be manually assigned any of the button color swatches from the theme to add visual contrast with
			| their container by adding the
			code  data-theme
			| attribute on the button markup and specifying a
			| swatch letter. When a link is added to a container, it is automatically assigned a theme swatch letter that
			| matches its parent bar or content box to visually integrate the button into the parent container, like a
			| chameleon.
		div(data-demo-html='true')
			p
				a(href='#', data-role='button', data-theme='a', data-inline='true') A
				a(href='#', data-role='button', data-theme='b', data-inline='true') B
				a(href='#', data-role='button', data-theme='c', data-inline='true') C
				a(href='#', data-role='button', data-theme='d', data-inline='true') D
				a(href='#', data-role='button', data-theme='e', data-inline='true') E
		h2#button-mini Mini
		p
			| For a more compact version that is useful in toolbars and tight spaces, add the
			code data-mini="true"
			| attribute to the button to create a mini version
			| .
		div(data-demo-html='true')
			p
				a(href='#', data-role='button', data-mini='true', data-inline='true') Cancel
				a(href='#', data-role='button', data-mini='true', data-inline='true', data-icon='check', data-theme='b')
					| Place
					| order
		h2#button-icons Icons
		p
			| An
			a(href='../icons/') icon
			| can be added to a button by adding a
			code  data-icon
			| attribute on
			| the anchor specifying the icon to display.
		div(data-demo-html='true')
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='plus', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true') Plus
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='minus', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true') Minus
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='delete', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true') Delete
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='arrow-l', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true')
				| Arrow
				| left
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='arrow-r', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true')
				| Arrow
				| right
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='arrow-u', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true')
				| Arrow
				| up
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='arrow-d', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true')
				| Arrow
				| down
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='check', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true') Check
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='gear', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true') Gear
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='refresh', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true') Refresh
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='forward', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true') Forward
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='back', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true') Back
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='grid', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true') Grid
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='star', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true') Star
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='alert', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true') Alert
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='info', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true') Info
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='home', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true') Home
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='search', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true') Search
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='bars', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true') Bars
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='edit', data-iconpos='notext', data-theme='c', data-inline='true') Edit
		h2#button-icon-position Icon position
		p
			| By default, all icons in buttons are placed to the left of the button text. This default may be overridden
			| using the
			code  data-iconpos
			| attribute to set the icon to the right, above (top) or below (bottom)
			| the text. You can also create an icon-only button, by setting the
			code  data-iconpos
			| attribute to
			code notext
			| . The button plugin will hide the text on-screen, but add it as a
			code title
			| attribute on the link to provide context for screen readers and devices that support tooltips.
		div(data-demo-html='true')
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-inline='true') Text only
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='arrow-l', data-iconpos='left', data-inline='true') Left
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='arrow-r', data-iconpos='right', data-inline='true') Right
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='arrow-u', data-iconpos='top', data-inline='true') Top
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='arrow-d', data-iconpos='bottom', data-inline='true') Bottom
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='delete', data-iconpos='notext', data-inline='true')
				| Icon
				| only
		h2#button-vertical-group Vertical group
		p
			| To visually group a set of buttons to form a single block, wrap a set of buttons in a container with the
			code  data-role="controlgroup"
			| attribute â€” the framework will create a vertical button group,
			| remove all margins and drop shadows between the buttons, and only round the first and last buttons of the
			| set to create the effect that they are grouped together.
		div(data-demo-html='true')
			div(data-role='controlgroup')
				a(href='#', data-role='button') Timeline
				a(href='#', data-role='button') Mentions
				a(href='#', data-role='button') Retweets
		h2#button-horizontal-group Horizontal group
		p
			| By adding the
			code data-type="horizontal"
			| attribute to the
			code controlgroup
			| container, you
			| can swap to a horizontal-style group that floats the buttons side-by-side and sets the width to only be
			| large enough to fit the content.
		div(data-demo-html='true')
			div(data-role='controlgroup', data-type='horizontal')
				a(href='#', data-role='button') Yes
				a(href='#', data-role='button') No
				a(href='#', data-role='button') Maybe
		p Mini horizontal grouped buttons, icon-only:
		div(data-demo-html='true')
			div(data-role='controlgroup', data-type='horizontal', data-mini='true')
				a(href='#', data-role='button', data-iconpos='notext', data-icon='plus', data-theme='b') Add
				a(href='#', data-role='button', data-iconpos='notext', data-icon='delete', data-theme='b') Delete
				a(href='#', data-role='button', data-iconpos='notext', data-icon='grid', data-theme='b') More
		h2#button-corners-shadows Corners & shadows
		p
			| There are options for controlling the rounded corners (
			code data-corners
			| ), drop shadow (
			code data-shadow
			| ),
			| and icon shadow for the highlight under the icon disc (
			code data-iconshadow
			| ).
		div(data-demo-html='true')
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='gear', data-theme='b') Default
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='gear', data-corners='false', data-theme='b')
				| No rounded
				| corners
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='gear', data-shadow='false', data-theme='b')
				| No button
				| shadow
			a(href='#', data-role='button', data-icon='gear', data-iconshadow='false', data-theme='b')
				| No icon
				| disc shadow
		h2 Disabled
		p
			| Form input or buttons can be disabled via the
			code disabled
			| attribute. Links styled like buttons have
			| all the same visual options as true form-based buttons, but aren't part of the
			code button
			| plugin so
			| the form button methods (enable, disable, refresh) aren't supported. If you need to disable a link-based
			| button (or any element), apply the disabled class ui-disabled yourself with JavaScript to achieve the same
			| effect.
		div(data-demo-html='true')
			a.ui-disabled(href='#', data-role='button') Disabled anchor via class
			form
				button(disabled='disabled') Button with disabled attribute
				input(type='button', value='Input with disabled attribute', disabled='disabled')

